  "doc_id": "12543",
  "text": "While the MoAb EGFR inhibitors lack many of the severe side effects commonly observed with cytotoxic chemotherapy, they are associated with a set of unique dermatological toxicities. The majority of patients treated with a MoAb EGFR inhibitor will experience dermatological side effects, most notably the papulopustular skin rash, which can impact quality of life and affect adherence to therapy [CITATION_1] .",
